title: First, use the change-of-base formula and choose $$k=5$$.

You should have $$\frac{\operatorname{log_5}\left(5\right)}{\operatorname{log_5}\left(11\right)}$$. $$\operatorname{log_5}\left(5\right)=1$$ since the logarithm of a number to its own base is $$1$$. Notice, $$\operatorname{log_5}\left(11\right)$$ is our given $$b$$.
